Document: GPUParticlesAttractorVectorField3D
Path: godot/classes/class_gpuparticlesattractorvectorfield3d.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring the 3D vector field attractor in GPU particles.

Property: size (Vector3): The size of the vector field box in 3D units. Default: Vector3(2, 2, 2). Methods: set_size(value: Vector3) → void, get_size() → Vector3.

Property: texture (Texture3D): The 3D texture to be used. Values are linearly interpolated between the texture's pixels. Note: To get better performance, the 3D texture's resolution should reflect the size of the attractor. Since particle attraction is usually low-frequency data, the texture can be kept at a low resolution such as 64×64×64. Methods: set_texture(value: Texture3D) → void, get_texture() → Texture3D.